embeds.title: Minion Master
embeds.description:
Rare Power / 2 :e_slime: / The Slime Boss / Downfall

 (**Innate**.)
Whenever you play a card with **Command,** **Command** again.

messages.content: I don't really see much how they would synergize tbh
other than it working at 0 cost, which I'm pretty sure it still would?
Minion master has a whole multitude of problems and issues, and it (possibly) no longer working with a 0 energy teamwork isn't really an issue

Reinforced body (7 block, upgrades to 9) is an easy point of comparison. It's lower block at all stages, so you really need to be getting value out of that command. If you have good slimes (usually that means leeching or mire) to take advantage, or extra potency to scale the effect, it gets better. Definitely worth taking if you have chem X, for a free 10 block and 2 commands at least. The good news for teamwork is that slime boss can struggle with finding enough block cards, so having a card that can saturate all your energy into block for a turn is valuable. There are probably block cards that do the job better (reformation for card selection, recollect for looping licks, sampling lick for the cantrip and cheap cost), but this is a good solution to a big attack if you only draw one block card that turn. 

As a rare, especially in slime boss, it has some stiff competition, and I can't imagine picking this over most of the other options unless I already had chem X. It's also worth noting that this is slime bosses only X cost card, which creates an awkward chicken and egg moment, where neither feels good to take on it's own while speculating on finding the other. Similarly, I wouldn't spend all the souls in a shop without chem X. The effect here is just too replaceable at lower rarities to be worth the opportunity cost. It doesn't even perform particularly well in act 1 if you get it from your heart bonus, since it really wants some intensity and good slimes for the command to be effective.

The upgrade, as with most X cards, is really solid, since it applies for every energy you spend on it. As soon as the start of act 2, I would look to upgrade this to make it more efficient, since you will need good block solutions to get through act 2 hallways and elites.

For a rare card this is very low impact. If you look at <press the attack> which is probably what it best compares to, I wouldn't consider that 5 block to be even close to comparable to the 9 damage, and when upgraded to the block is 8 then you aren't getting a good deal with command.
